Vehicle evaluation group True Price provides new data on cars with the best resale value in South Africa. The group’s data is gathered from thousands of vehicles sold on auction around the country. “To determine which passenger cars have the best resale value, we analysed all our data and came up with a list of the top 10 cars,” said Darryl Jacobson, MD of True Price. “This list is based on actual prices achieved on auction. The figures pertain to the percentage of original selling price that has been achieved on auction,” he said. Jacobson stressed that resale value is an essential consideration when buying a new car. “Depreciation is one of the new car buyer’s greatest expenses. It is absolutely vital to take resale value into consideration before signing on the dotted line,” he said. Below is a list of the 10 vehicles with the best resale value and how much they cost to buy new. Renault Kwid – from R132,500 <img class="size-full wp-image-274663 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/kWID1.jpeg" alt="" width="1000" height="700" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/kWID1.jpeg 1000w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/kWID1-300x210.jpeg 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/kWID1-768x538.jpeg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px" /> Toyota Etios – from R179,500 <img class="size-full wp-image-304304 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/ToyotaEtios-e1552034825786.jpg" alt="" width="1200" height="801" /> Volkswagen Polo – from R216,300 <img class="size-full wp-image-262271 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/VWPolo.jpg" alt="" width="1400" height="784" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/VWPolo.jpg 1400w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/VWPolo-300x168.jpg 300